        "value": 20,
        "unit": "ns",
        "description": "Nanosecond regime preferred for cleaning to ablate contaminants while minimizing heat-affected zone (HAZ); picosecond (ps) or femtosecond (fs) for ultra-precise but costlier applications. 20 ns recommended for Praseodymium to limit thermal diffusion due to low conductivity. From laser physics research on metal ablation thresholds (Applied Surface Science, 2015); ns pulses common for industrial cleaning."
      },
